jqPlot

JavaScript plotting library for jQuery.

Summary
jqPlotJavaScript plotting library for jQuery.
CopyrightCopyright © 2009 Chris Leonello
LicenseLicensed under the MIT License.
Axis[Private] An individual axis object.
Properties
nameAxis name (identifier).
showWether to display the axis on the graph.
scaleFactor to multiply by the data range when setting the axis bounds
numberTicksDesired number of ticks.
tickIntervalnumber of units between ticks.
rendererreference to a rendering engine that draws the axis on the plot.
labelAxis label object.
ticksContainer for axis ticks and their properties.
tickFormatterFunction applied to format tick label text.
_heightheight of the rendered axis in pixels.
_widthwidth of the rendered axis in pixels.
_elemreference to the actual axis DOM element.
_dataBoundslow/high values of all of the series bound to this axis.
maxmaximum value of the axis (in data units, not pixels).
styleDon’t know? 
_gridOffsetsreference to the plot element grid offsets.
_offsetsPixel offsets from the edge of the DOM element in pixels.
_canvasWidthwidth of the grid canvas, total DOM element width.
_canvasHeightheight of the grid canvas, total DOM element height.
Legend[Private] Legend object.
Properties
showWether to display the legend on the graph.
locationPlacement of the legend.
xoffsetoffset from the inside edge of the plot in the x direction in pixels.
yoffsetoffset from the inside edge of the plot in the y direction in pixels.
bordercss spec for the border around the legend box.
backgroundcss spec for the background of the legend box.
textColorcss color spec for the legend text.
fontFamilycss font-family spec for the legend text.
fontSizecss font-size spec for the legend text.
rowSpacingcss padding-top spec for the rows in the legend.
_elemreference to the legend DOM element.
Title[Private] Plot Title object.
Properties
texttext of the title;
fontFamilycss font-family spec for the text.
fontSizecss font-size spec for the text.
textAligncss text-align spec for the text.
_elemreference to the title DOM element.
_heightheight of the DOM element in pixels.
_widthwidth of the DOM element in pixels.
textColorcss color spec for the text.
Series[Private] An individual data series object.
Properties
showwether or not to draw the series.
xaxisname of x axis to associate with this series.
_xaxisreference to the underlying x axis object associated with this series.
yaxisname of y axis to associate with this series.
_yaxisreference to the underlying y axis object associated with this series.
rendererreference to a renderer which will actually draw this series.
dataraw user data points.
gridDatadata in grid coordinates.
lineWidthwidth of the line in pixels.
shadowwether or not to draw a shadow on the line
shadowAngleShadow angle in degrees
shadowOffsetShadow offset from line in pixels
shadowDepthNumber of times shadow is stroked, each stroke offset shadowOffset from the last.
shadowAlphaAlpha channel transparency of shadow.
breakOnNullwether line segments should be be broken at null value.
labelLine label to use in legend.
Grid[Private] Object representing the grid on which the plot is drawn.
Properties
drawGridlineswether to draw the gridlines on the plot.
backgroundcss spec for the background color.
borderColorcss spec for the color of the grid border.
borderWidthwidth of the border in pixels.
shadowwether to show a shadow behind the grid.
shadowAngleshadow angle in degrees
shadowOffsetOffset of each shadow stroke from the border in pixels
shadowWidthwidth of the stoke for the shadow
shadowDepthNumber of times shadow is stroked, each stroke offset shadowOffset from the last.
shadowAlphaAlpha channel transparency of shadow.
_widthwidth of the grid area bounded by the border.
_heightheight of the grid area bounded by the border.
_topposition of the top of the grid measures from the top left of the DOM container.
_bottomposition of the bottom of the grid measures from the top left of the DOM container.
_leftposition of the left of the grid measures from the top left of the DOM container.
_rightposition of the right of the grid measures from the top left of the DOM container.
rendererreference to the object which will actually render the grid.
jqPlot[Private] Plot object returned to call to $.jqplot.
Functions
initInitializes the jqPlot object, parsing the user options and processing the data.
parseOptionsParses the user’s options overriding defaults.
drawCalls functions needed to draw the plot.
drawTitleDraws the plot title
drawAxesDraws the axes on the plot.
packDimensions an positions the grid and axes.
drawLegendDraws the legend on top of the grid.
drawSeriesCalls the series renderer for each series in the plot within the context of the individual series.
$.jqplotjQuery extension called by user to create plot.
Variables
$.jqplot.postParseOptionsHooksArray of plugin hooks run after jqPlot.parseOptions method
$.jqplot.postDrawHooksArray of plugin hooks run after jqPlot.draw method
$.jqplot.postDrawSeriesHooksArray of plugin hooks run after each series renderer’s draw method is called in jqPlot.drawSeries method.
$.jqplot.drawLegendHooksArray of plugin hooks run within but at the end of the jqPlot.drawLegend method.
$.jqplot.canvasGridRendererRendrer for a jqPlot object which draws the grid as a canvas element on the page.
Functions

Axis

[Private] An individual axis object.  Cannot be instantiated directly, but created by the Plot oject.  Axis properties can be set or overriden by the options passed in from the user.

Parameters

nameAxis name (identifier).  One of ‘xaxis’, ‘yaxis’, ‘x2axis’ or ‘y2axis’.
Summary
Properties
nameAxis name (identifier).
showWether to display the axis on the graph.
scaleFactor to multiply by the data range when setting the axis bounds
numberTicksDesired number of ticks.
tickIntervalnumber of units between ticks.
rendererreference to a rendering engine that draws the axis on the plot.
labelAxis label object.
ticksContainer for axis ticks and their properties.
tickFormatterFunction applied to format tick label text.
_heightheight of the rendered axis in pixels.
_widthwidth of the rendered axis in pixels.
_elemreference to the actual axis DOM element.
_dataBoundslow/high values of all of the series bound to this axis.
maxmaximum value of the axis (in data units, not pixels).
styleDon’t know? 
_gridOffsetsreference to the plot element grid offsets.
_offsetsPixel offsets from the edge of the DOM element in pixels.
_canvasWidthwidth of the grid canvas, total DOM element width.
_canvasHeightheight of the grid canvas, total DOM element height.

Properties

name

this.name = name

Axis name (identifier).  One of ‘xaxis’, ‘yaxis’, ‘x2axis’ or ‘y2axis’.

show

this.show = false

Wether to display the axis on the graph.

scale

this.scale = 1.2

Factor to multiply by the data range when setting the axis bounds

numberTicks

this.numberTicks

Desired number of ticks.  Computed automatically by default

tickInterval

this.tickInterval

number of units between ticks.  Mutually exclusive with numberTicks.

renderer

this.renderer = new $.jqplot.lineAxisRenderer()

reference to a rendering engine that draws the axis on the plot.

label

this.label = {text:null, fontFamily:null, fontSize:null, align:null}

Axis label object.  Container for axis label properties.  Not implimeted yet.

Properties

textlabel text.
fontFamilycss font-family spec.
fontSizecss font-size spec.
aligncss text-align spec.

ticks

this.ticks = {mark:'outside', size:4, showLabels:true, labels:[], values:[], styles:[], formatString:'%.1f', fontFamily:'', fontSize:'0.75em', textColor:''}

Container for axis ticks and their properties.

Properties

marktick markings.  One of ‘inside’, ‘outside’, ‘cross’, ‘’ or null.  The latter 2 options will hide the tick marks.
sizelength of the tick marks in pixels.  For ‘cross’ style, length will be stoked above and below axis, so total length will be twice this.
showLabelsWether to show labels or not.
labelsArray of tick labels.
valuesArray of underlying data values.
stylesArray of css styles to be applied.
formatStringformatting string passed to the tick formatter.
fontFamilycss font-family spec. fontSize -css font-size spec.
textColorcss color spec.

tickFormatter

this.tickFormatter = sprintf

Function applied to format tick label text.

_height

this._height = 0

height of the rendered axis in pixels.

_width

this._width = 0

width of the rendered axis in pixels.

_elem

this._elem

reference to the actual axis DOM element.

_dataBounds

this._dataBounds = {min:null, max:null}

low/high values of all of the series bound to this axis.

Properties

minlowest value on this axis.
maxhighest value on this axis.

max

this.max=null

maximum value of the axis (in data units, not pixels).

style

this.style

Don’t know?  Will have to check if this is used.

_gridOffsets

this._gridOffsets

reference to the plot element grid offsets.

_offsets

this._offsets = {min:null, max:null}

Pixel offsets from the edge of the DOM element in pixels.

Properties

minpixel offset to the minimum value.
maxpixel offset to the maximum value.

_canvasWidth

this._canvasWidth

width of the grid canvas, total DOM element width.

_canvasHeight

this._canvasHeight

height of the grid canvas, total DOM element height.

Legend

[Private] Legend object.  Cannot be instantiated directly, but created by the Plot oject.  Legend properties can be set or overriden by the options passed in from the user.

Summary
Properties
showWether to display the legend on the graph.
locationPlacement of the legend.
xoffsetoffset from the inside edge of the plot in the x direction in pixels.
yoffsetoffset from the inside edge of the plot in the y direction in pixels.
bordercss spec for the border around the legend box.
backgroundcss spec for the background of the legend box.
textColorcss color spec for the legend text.
fontFamilycss font-family spec for the legend text.
fontSizecss font-size spec for the legend text.
rowSpacingcss padding-top spec for the rows in the legend.
_elemreference to the legend DOM element.

Properties

show

this.show = true

Wether to display the legend on the graph.

location

this.location = 'se'

Placement of the legend.  one of the compas directions: nw, n, ne, e, se, s, sw, w

xoffset

this.xoffset = 12

offset from the inside edge of the plot in the x direction in pixels.

yoffset

this.yoffset = 12

offset from the inside edge of the plot in the y direction in pixels.

border

this.border = '1px solid #cccccc'

css spec for the border around the legend box.

background

this.background = 'rgba(255,255,255,0.6)'

css spec for the background of the legend box.

textColor

this.textColor = ''

css color spec for the legend text.

fontFamily

this.fontFamily = ''

css font-family spec for the legend text.

fontSize

this.fontSize = '0.75em'

css font-size spec for the legend text.

rowSpacing

this.rowSpacing = '0.5em'

css padding-top spec for the rows in the legend.

_elem

this._elem

reference to the legend DOM element.

Series

[Private] An individual data series object.  Cannot be instantiated directly, but created by the Plot oject.  Series properties can be set or overriden by the options passed in from the user.

Summary
Properties
showwether or not to draw the series.
xaxisname of x axis to associate with this series.
_xaxisreference to the underlying x axis object associated with this series.
yaxisname of y axis to associate with this series.
_yaxisreference to the underlying y axis object associated with this series.
rendererreference to a renderer which will actually draw this series.
dataraw user data points.
gridDatadata in grid coordinates.
lineWidthwidth of the line in pixels.
shadowwether or not to draw a shadow on the line
shadowAngleShadow angle in degrees
shadowOffsetShadow offset from line in pixels
shadowDepthNumber of times shadow is stroked, each stroke offset shadowOffset from the last.
shadowAlphaAlpha channel transparency of shadow.
breakOnNullwether line segments should be be broken at null value.
labelLine label to use in legend.

Properties

show

this.show = true

wether or not to draw the series.

xaxis

this.xaxis = 'xaxis'

name of x axis to associate with this series.

_xaxis

this._xaxis = new Axis(this.xaxis)

reference to the underlying x axis object associated with this series.

yaxis

this.yaxis = 'yaxis'

name of y axis to associate with this series.

_yaxis

this._yaxis = new Axis(this.yaxis)

reference to the underlying y axis object associated with this series.

renderer

this.renderer = new $.jqplot.lineRenderer()

reference to a renderer which will actually draw this series.

data

this.data = []

raw user data points.  These should never be altered!!!

gridData

this.gridData = []

data in grid coordinates.  User data transformed for plotting on grid.

lineWidth

this.lineWidth = 2.5

width of the line in pixels.  May have different meanings depending on renderer.

shadow

this.shadow = true

wether or not to draw a shadow on the line

shadowAngle

this.shadowAngle = 45

Shadow angle in degrees

shadowOffset

this.shadowOffset = 1

Shadow offset from line in pixels

shadowDepth

this.shadowDepth = 3

Number of times shadow is stroked, each stroke offset shadowOffset from the last.

shadowAlpha

this.shadowAlpha = '0.07'

Alpha channel transparency of shadow.  0 = transparent.

breakOnNull

this.breakOnNull = false

wether line segments should be be broken at null value.  False will join point on either side of line.

label

this.label = ''

Line label to use in legend.

Grid

[Private] Object representing the grid on which the plot is drawn.  The grid in this context is the area bounded by the axes, the area which will contain the series.  The Grid object cannot be instantiated directly, but is created by the Plot oject.  Grid properties can be set or overriden by the options passed in from the user.

Summary
Properties
drawGridlineswether to draw the gridlines on the plot.
backgroundcss spec for the background color.
borderColorcss spec for the color of the grid border.
borderWidthwidth of the border in pixels.
shadowwether to show a shadow behind the grid.
shadowAngleshadow angle in degrees
shadowOffsetOffset of each shadow stroke from the border in pixels
shadowWidthwidth of the stoke for the shadow
shadowDepthNumber of times shadow is stroked, each stroke offset shadowOffset from the last.
shadowAlphaAlpha channel transparency of shadow.
_widthwidth of the grid area bounded by the border.
_heightheight of the grid area bounded by the border.
_topposition of the top of the grid measures from the top left of the DOM container.
_bottomposition of the bottom of the grid measures from the top left of the DOM container.
_leftposition of the left of the grid measures from the top left of the DOM container.
_rightposition of the right of the grid measures from the top left of the DOM container.
rendererreference to the object which will actually render the grid.

Properties

drawGridlines

this.drawGridlines = true

wether to draw the gridlines on the plot.

background

this.background = '#fffdf6'

css spec for the background color.

borderColor

this.borderColor = '#999999'

css spec for the color of the grid border.

borderWidth

this.borderWidth = 2.0

width of the border in pixels.

shadow

this.shadow = true

wether to show a shadow behind the grid.

shadowAngle

this.shadowAngle = 45

shadow angle in degrees

shadowOffset

this.shadowOffset = 1.5

Offset of each shadow stroke from the border in pixels

shadowWidth

this.shadowWidth = 3

width of the stoke for the shadow

shadowDepth

this.shadowDepth = 3

Number of times shadow is stroked, each stroke offset shadowOffset from the last.

shadowAlpha

this.shadowAlpha = '0.07'

Alpha channel transparency of shadow.  0 = transparent.

_width

this._width

width of the grid area bounded by the border.

_height

this._height

height of the grid area bounded by the border.

_top

this._top

position of the top of the grid measures from the top left of the DOM container.

_bottom

this._bottom

position of the bottom of the grid measures from the top left of the DOM container.

_left

this._left

position of the left of the grid measures from the top left of the DOM container.

_right

this._right

position of the right of the grid measures from the top left of the DOM container.

renderer

this.renderer = new $.jqplot.canvasGridRenderer()

reference to the object which will actually render the grid.

jqPlot

[Private] Plot object returned to call to $.jqplot.  Handles parsing user options, creating sub objects (Axes, legend, title, series) and rendering the plot.

Summary
Functions
initInitializes the jqPlot object, parsing the user options and processing the data.
parseOptionsParses the user’s options overriding defaults.
drawCalls functions needed to draw the plot.
drawTitleDraws the plot title
drawAxesDraws the axes on the plot.
packDimensions an positions the grid and axes.
drawLegendDraws the legend on top of the grid.
drawSeriesCalls the series renderer for each series in the plot within the context of the individual series.

Functions

init

this.init = function(target,
data,
options)

Initializes the jqPlot object, parsing the user options and processing the data.

Parameter

targetID of the DOM element the plot will render into.
datadata series.
optionsuser specified options object.

parseOptions

this.parseOptions = function(options)

Parses the user’s options overriding defaults.

Parameters

optionsoptions object passed into $.jqplot by user.

draw

this.draw = function()

Calls functions needed to draw the plot.

drawTitle

this.drawTitle = function()

Draws the plot title

drawAxes

this.drawAxes = function()

Draws the axes on the plot.

pack

this.pack = function()

Dimensions an positions the grid and axes.

drawLegend

this.drawLegend = function()

Draws the legend on top of the grid.  Renders it as a table.

drawSeries

this.drawSeries = function()

Calls the series renderer for each series in the plot within the context of the individual series.

$.jqplot

jQuery extension called by user to create plot.

Parameters

targetID of target element to render the plot into.
dataan array of data series.
optionsuser defined options object.
Summary
Variables
$.jqplot.postParseOptionsHooksArray of plugin hooks run after jqPlot.parseOptions method
$.jqplot.postDrawHooksArray of plugin hooks run after jqPlot.draw method
$.jqplot.postDrawSeriesHooksArray of plugin hooks run after each series renderer’s draw method is called in jqPlot.drawSeries method.
$.jqplot.drawLegendHooksArray of plugin hooks run within but at the end of the jqPlot.drawLegend method.

Variables

$.jqplot.postParseOptionsHooks

$.jqplot.postParseOptionsHooks

Array of plugin hooks run after jqPlot.parseOptions method

$.jqplot.postDrawHooks

$.jqplot.postDrawHooks

Array of plugin hooks run after jqPlot.draw method

$.jqplot.postDrawSeriesHooks

$.jqplot.postDrawSeriesHooks

Array of plugin hooks run after each series renderer’s draw method is called in jqPlot.drawSeries method.

$.jqplot.drawLegendHooks

$.jqplot.drawLegendHooks

Array of plugin hooks run within but at the end of the jqPlot.drawLegend method.

$.jqplot.canvasGridRenderer

Rendrer for a jqPlot object which draws the grid as a canvas element on the page.

Summary
Functions

Functions

createDrawingContext

$.jqplot.canvasGridRenderer.prototype.createDrawingContext = function()

Creates (but doesn’t populate) the actual canvas elements for plotting.  Called within context of jqPlot object.
